---
// Landing page for the Payment Engine portfolio piece.
// Per .bocek/vault/2026-04-26-surface-architecture-landing-page.md:
// - First-impression surface for any audience including non-technical
// - Embed Loom further down (deep dive); hero uses asciinema-curl cast
// - Cross-link to GitHub README + live API + Loom

const GITHUB_URL = "https://github.com/USER/payment-engine"; // TODO: set
const LIVE_API_URL = "https://payment-engine.up.railway.app"; // TODO: confirm after Railway deploy
const LOOM_EMBED_URL = "https://www.loom.com/embed/PLACEHOLDER"; // TODO: replace after recording
const ASCIINEMA_CAST_URL = "https://asciinema.org/a/PLACEHOLDER"; // TODO: replace after recording
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Payment Engine — Production-grade double-entry ledger</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A payment processor with a double-entry accounting ledger. 447 tests, BigInt money, race-safe idempotency, multi-capture authorization."
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #0d1117;
        --fg: #e6edf3;
        --muted: #7d8590;
        --accent: #2f81f7;
        --green: #3fb950;
        --border: #30363d;
        --card: #161b22;
        --mono: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, "SF Mono", Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Menlo, monospace;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--fg);
        font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 880px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
      }
      header h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }
      header .tagline {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0 0 2rem;
        max-width: 60ch;
      }
      .ctas {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      }
      .btn {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;
        border-radius: 6px;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        transition: opacity 0.15s;
      }
      .btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }
      .btn-primary {
        background: var(--accent);
        color: #fff;
      }
      .btn-secondary {
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--fg);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .metrics {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
        margin: 2rem 0 3rem;
      }
      .metric {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 1.25rem;
      }
      .metric .num {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        color: var(--green);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .metric .label {
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-top: 0.25rem;
      }
      .asciinema {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        overflow-x: auto;
        margin: 2rem 0;
      }
      .asciinema .prompt { color: var(--muted); }
      .asciinema .ok { color: var(--green); }
      h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin: 3rem 0 1rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .arch-diagram {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        color: var(--fg);
        overflow-x: auto;
        white-space: pre;
        line-height: 1.4;
      }
      .case-study {
        background: var(--card);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
        border-radius: 4px;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
      }
      .case-study h3 {
        margin-top: 0;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      pre, code {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 0.85em;
      }
      .loom-embed {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        padding-bottom: 62.5%;
        height: 0;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .loom-embed iframe {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        border: 0;
      }
      footer {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        padding-top: 2rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      footer a { color: var(--accent); }
      ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
      li { margin: 0.35rem 0; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="container">
      <header>
        <h1>Payment Engine</h1>
        <p class="tagline">
          A production-grade payment processor with a double-entry ledger.
          Authorize → capture → settle → refund, every cent balanced, every
          retry safe.
        </p>
        <div class="ctas">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href={LIVE_API_URL + "/docs"}>Try the API</a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={GITHUB_URL}>View source on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>The numbers</h2>
        <div class="metrics">
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="num">447 tests</div>
            <div class="label">unit · integration · e2e · property · fuzz · reconciliation</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="num">~3000</div>
            <div class="label"><code>expect()</code> calls covering every spec invariant</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="num">God check</div>
            <div class="label">runs after every integration test: SUM(debits) === SUM(credits)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="num">0 floats</div>
            <div class="label">BigInt money throughout the engine</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="num">7 decisions</div>
            <div class="label">recorded in vault with rejected alternatives</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="num">19.4ms</div>
            <div class="label">authorize p50 (Railway → Supabase EU, vitest bench)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Live demo</h2>
        <p>
          Real terminal hitting the live engine on Railway. Authorize $150,
          capture, view the balanced ledger, watch the god check pass.
        </p>
        <div class="asciinema">
          <p><a href={ASCIINEMA_CAST_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            ▶ Open asciinema cast →
          </a></p>
          <p style="color: var(--muted); margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.8rem;">
            <em>Cast embed pending recording against live Railway deploy.
            See <code>scripts/record-demo.sh</code> in the repo.</em>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Architecture</h2>
        <pre class="arch-diagram">{`
HTTP request
     │
     ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────┐
│  Hono routes (Zod-validated)     │
│  src/payments/routes.ts          │
│  src/ledger/routes.ts            │
└──────────┬───────────────────────┘
           │
           ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────┐
│  Service layer                   │
│  src/payments/service.ts         │ ◀── state machine
│  src/ledger/service.ts           │     (8 states, 13 transitions)
└──────────┬───────────────────────┘
           │
           ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────┐
│  Idempotency claim               │
│  INSERT ... ON CONFLICT          │ ◀── race-safe per-mutation
│  DO NOTHING RETURNING            │     (5 endpoints)
└──────────┬───────────────────────┘
           │
           ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────┐
│  Drizzle (Postgres)              │
│  Direct conn :5432 (NOT pooled)  │ ◀── pessimistic locking
│  Supabase EU-West-1              │     (SELECT ... FOR UPDATE)
└──────────────────────────────────┘
        `.trim()}</pre>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Walkthrough</h2>
        <p>
          Two-minute Loom: 60 seconds on a financial bug found and fixed
          (partial-refund double-refund), 60 seconds on the architecture
          model.
        </p>
        <div class="loom-embed">
          <iframe
            src={LOOM_EMBED_URL}
            frameborder="0"
            webkitallowfullscreen
            mozallowfullscreen
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Bug found and fixed</h2>
        <div class="case-study">
          <h3>Partial-refund double-refund</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Symptom:</strong> a network retry of a successful partial
            refund could double-refund. Same idempotency key, second call
            sees the payment in <code>partially_refunded</code> state,
            validates that <code>refundedAmount + retryAmount ≤ capturedAmount</code>,
            and executes again. Real money out, twice, no error to the
            client.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Root cause:</strong> the route layer required an
            <code>Idempotency-Key</code> header but the service layer never
            received it. Same was true for capture, void, and settle — all
            four mutations.
          </p>
          <p><strong>Fix in TDD order:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Wrote 4 failing tests asserting the contract: same-key retry returns identical refund, no extra ledger entries, full-refund retry returns original 200, different-amount-same-key returns 409.</li>
            <li>Built a race-safe idempotency claim in <code>src/shared/idempotency.ts</code> using <code>INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING RETURNING</code> — atomic, no TOCTOU window.</li>
            <li>Wired the key through every mutation including signature changes across ~80 call sites in tests + factories.</li>
            <li>All 4 tests turned green. Full suite confirmed no regressions. Added 12 retry tests across all 4 mutations and replaced 4 vacuous "retry" tests that passed by accident.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Stack</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> Bun (production)</li>
          <li><strong>API:</strong> Hono + <code>@hono/zod-openapi</code> (Scalar UI at <code>/docs</code>)</li>
          <li><strong>Database:</strong> PostgreSQL — Docker for tests, Supabase for production</li>
          <li><strong>ORM:</strong> Drizzle</li>
          <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Zod (also generates the OpenAPI 3.1 spec)</li>
          <li><strong>Tests:</strong> Vitest (correctness) + <code>vitest bench</code> (perf, separated)</li>
          <li><strong>Money:</strong> BigInt throughout — zero floating point</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <footer>
        <p>
          <a href={GITHUB_URL}>GitHub</a> · <a href={LIVE_API_URL + "/docs"}>API docs</a> · <a href={LOOM_EMBED_URL}>Walkthrough</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          Built to understand fintech from the ground up.
          Architectural decisions in <code>.bocek/vault/</code>.
        </p>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
